===Etymology===
From {{LL.}} {{term|Philistinus|lang=la}}, from Late {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|Φυλιστῖνοι|tr=Phulistinoi|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{etyl|he|en}} {{term|פלשתים|tr=P'lishtim|lang=he|sc=Hebr}} from {{term|פלשת||Philistia|tr=P'leshet|lang=he|sc=Hebr}} {{rfscript|Hebrew|Could we get some vowel marks?}}.  The transition from nationality to one lacking education/culture took place in the early 19th century (in English) and is not fully explained.  

